<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-04-14T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-04-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="400" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d400">
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Minister in the Netherlands</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_VDH1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Van
                                    Dyke</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-04-14">
                                        <hi rend="italic">April 14, 1915</hi>.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>142. British Embassy notifies Department tobacco, cocoa, and coffee
                                destined to Holland must be consigned to Overseas Trust. Has
                                Overseas Trust now authority to receive consignments non-contraband
                                goods?</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_BWJ1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>